    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen I open the editor, the lines rendering is skewed by one line, resulting in all sorts of visual issues and an unusable editor. \n\nVisually, it looks like this:\n<img width=\"1277\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eed49eb4-e6b8-4b90-947e-a9cc5a1501d1\" />\nNotice the line numbering starts at 2 and the status line is split on two lines.\n\nIf I disable vim-airline, the behaviour doesn't occur anymore:\n<img width=\"1276\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d7aa3e78-7a7a-4123-b95b-4721ad73e413\" />\n\nNote that the issue is not always reproducible and seems somewhat dependent on the terminal settings. I could only reproduce the issue on macOS and while inside tmux. I reproduced it in multiple terminal emulators: kitty, ghostty and iTerm2.\n\nI can workaround the issue by unsetting the `TMUX` env var and by setting `TERM=xterm-256color` (instead of `tmux-256color`).\n\nI isolated the source of the problem to this commit: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/2613ba5000d4c0d9b15e2eec2d2b97615575925e. Note that the issue does _not_ happen on master. I am still opening this issue because I imagine that this commit could make its way to the master branch eventually.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUse this configuration\n```lua\n-- Run this file as `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n\nfor name, url in pairs {\n  'https://github.com/vim-airline/vim-airline/',\n} do\n  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify('nvim_issue/' .. name, ':p')\n  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\n    vim.fn.system { 'git', 'clone', '--depth=1', url, install_path }\n  end\n  vim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)\nend\n\n-- ADD INIT.LUA SETTINGS _NECESSARY_ FOR REPRODUCING THE ISSUE\nvim.opt.number = true  -- Not necessary, but shows the issue much better\n```\n\nAnd this sample foo.diff file. It contains a trailing space at line 7 which is needed for the issue\n```diff\ndiff --git a/main.go b/main.go\nindex 91e7378..a282cd2 100644\n--- a/main.go\n+++ b/main.go\n@@ -3,5 +3,5 @@ package main\n import \"fmt\"\n \n func main() {\n-\tfmt.Println(\"Hello World\")\n+\tfmt.Println(\"Goodbye World\")\n }\n```\n\nRun `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua foo.diff`. Notice the line numbering starts at 2\n\nPress `VG` to highlight the whole document. Notice the lines update incorrectly.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe file should be displayed properly. See expected image in the description above.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.754\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.38.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
